703: // getSwaggerSpec loads and caches the swagger spec. If a cached version already exists,
704: // it returns the cached one. The reason why we cache it is because some downstream projects
705: // (e.g. Grafana Mimir) creates many Alertmanager instances in the same process, so they would
706: // incur in a significant memory penalty if we would reload the swagger spec each time.
